models.name: joseph 1
models.description:
This is your scan from Wednesday 16th April 2014 at Making It ... at the Museum. We hope you had a great time at our new exhibition.

Just view yourself in the 'Thingiviewer' to see how cool you look in all 3 dimensions, or download yourself as an .stl file. 
To look at your 3D self on your computer you will need to download an .stl viewer - there are lots of  open-source .stl viewers available online for free. Search for 'free stl viewer' to find one for yourself.

models.name: Starhawk-Class Battleship (Kitbash)
models.description:
WORK IN PROGRESS

My interpretation of a Nadiri Mk1 Starhawk.
http://starwars.wikia.com/wiki/Starhawk-class_battleship

Length: 1331 meters

Design philsophy:
- Can take on an Imperial Star Destroyer unassisted
- Rebuilt from a captured Star Destroyer in line with the ship lore
- Not as versatile as a Star Destroyer (reduced starfighter capacity, removal of group troop capacity)

models.name: Sphinx rep-tile
models.description:
This is the Sphinx rep-tile, four units of which create a larger version of the same tile.  The sphinx is the best-known pentagonal rep-tile.

The scale, width of the outline,  the extruded height and form are customisable
